06/12/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The 12th annual meeting of the OSCE's Ministerial Council, under the chairmanship of Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, began in Sofia on Monday (6 December).
Over 40 top diplomats and 70 delegations from OSCE member countries and partners are attending the two-day event, amid heightened security.
Bulgaria assumed the rotating OSCE presidency at the start of start of the year.
Slovenia will assume the presidency next.
(bTV, Dnevnik - 06/12/04)
